benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to bundle

covered: Valid Request: Successful updates with proper headers and body (TC01, TC02, TC17, TC23, TC25).
Non-Existing Resource: Handling of 404 for nonexistent bundle (TC05).
Authorization and Headers: Handling of missing required header (TC06) and unauthorized access (TC10).
Error Handling: 400 responses for invalid bundleId (TC04), malformed body (TC07), missing body (TC08), and unsupported fields (TC09).
Validation and Security: 400 for SQL injection attempt (TC12), 400 for malformed input, handling special characters (TC19).
Edge Cases: Tests for max fields (TC13), max value length (TC14), empty value (TC15), extra URL param (TC16).
State Variation: Tests for no existing fields (TC22), updates on existing fields (TC23), partial updates (TC24).
Performance: Under normal and peak load tests (TC17, TC18).
Integration/Resilience: Dependency inconsistency (TC20) and transient network recovery (TC21).
Backward Compatibility and Regression: Tests for older clients (TC25).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not tested.
Additional authorization edge cases (invalid/expired tokens) not tested.
Explicit race-condition coverage beyond high-concurrency test (e.g., deterministic concurrent updates with conflict resolution) not detailed.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests and simulate multiple rapid requests.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers behavior.
Add tests for invalid/expired tokens and insufficient permissions.
Enhance concurrency testing with explicit race-condition scenarios and conflict resolution checks.
